Package edu.harvard.hul.ois.fits

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AESModel  
    DocumentMDModel  
    DocumentTypes
    A class with static methods for managing document types.
    EbuCoreFrameRateRatio
    This class handles the creation of a numerator and denominator for a Video Frame Rate, based upon the value passed in, as well as the transformation of actual the value passed in based upon the following logic: If FrameRate from MediaInfo is a whole number, then the following is true: frameRate = the value remains the same numerator = 1 denominator = 1 Otherwise the following is true: frameRate = the value is rounded to the nearest whole integer numerator = 1000 denominator = 1001 For example, if the value passed in is 20, then both the the numerator and denominator are set to 1, and the frame rate is unchanged (20).
    EbuCoreModel  
    EbuCoreNormalizedRatio
    This class handles the transformation of the numerator and denominator contained within a Ratio used in Ebucore XML to normalized values.
    Fits
    The main class for FITS.
    FitsMetadataElement  
    FitsMetadataValues
    This class holds standard element names for FITS metadata output, as well as some standard values.
    FitsOutput
    This class acts as a wrapper aroudn the fitsXML JDOM Document and provides convenience methods for converting the FITS XML format to standard technical metdata schemas, accessing identification, file info, and metadata elements
    MixModel
    This class represents a Mix object, with various convenient functions for use by XmlContentConverter in building up the structure.
    TextMDModel  
    XmlContentConverter
